          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1172_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;brioche rolls</strong> to a baking tray</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until the brioche is warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1172.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1172.step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1172.step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1172.step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1172.step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>baby gammon</strong> is done, transfer it to a board and shred it, using two forks &ndash; this technique is known as 'pulling'</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> pulled ham</strong> to the<strong>&nbsp;barbecue&nbsp;sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
